# ---- Python ----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ---- Virtual environments ----
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ---- Environment / secrets ----
.env
.env.*
# The key TEMPLATE is committed; only files holding real keys are ignored.
!.env.example

# ---- IDE (JetBrains / VS Code) ----
# Ignore IDE *state* (workspace.xml, caches, per-machine SDK paths) but SHIP the run
# configurations: the numbered ladder 0_estimate -> 9_status IS the pipeline, and the
# brief asks for something runnable from scratch. Note this must ignore .idea's CONTENTS,
# not the directory — git will not descend into an ignored directory to find the negation.
.idea/*
.vscode/

# ---- OS cruft ----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ---- Raw data (large binary PDFs) ----
# The 13 hospital source PDFs (fictional ground truth) ARE committed — the pipeline
# needs them and they exist nowhere public. The 15 medical PDFs are large, public
# CDC/ECDC reports used only as RAG distractors: re-download rather than bloat git.
data/raw/medical/

# ---- Downloaded checkpoint archives ----
# The Together adapter arrives as a ~158 MB .tar.zst which we extract into
# models/<producer>/. The archive is a re-downloadable cache, not a deliverable, and it
# is larger than GitHub's 100 MB per-file limit — keep it out of git.
models/*.tar.zst